## SHotkeysListComponent

Simply list the registered hotkeys stored in the document.env.HOTKEYS stack and update itself on the 'hotkey.update' event. Works fine with the `__hotkey` function from \"@coffeekraken/sugar/dom\" package.

## Features

-   Framework agnostic. Simply webcomponent.
-   List all the registered hotkeys from the document.env.HOTKEYS stack.
-   Works fine with the `__hotkey` function from \"@coffeekraken/sugar/dom\" package.
-   And more...

## Usage

First, simply import and define the component in your js/ts file:

```js
import { __define } from '@coffeekraken/s-hotkeys-list-component';
__define();
```

Make use of it in your pages:

```html
<s-hotkeys-list></s-hotkeys-list>
```

